'''Iain McCaig''' is an artistic director, concept designer, and filmmaker who worked at JAK Films, a division of [[Lucasfilm]], as a storyboard and concept artist for Episodes I, II, III and VII.<ref name="Insider 145">{{InsiderCite|145|Shaping the Past}}</ref> Several of the characters he designed include [[Darth Maul/Legends|Darth Maul]], [[Padmé Amidala/Legends|Queen Amidala]], and [[Sio Bibble/Legends|Sio Bibble]]. Artwork by McCaig was also featured in ''[[A New Hope: The Princess, the Scoundrel, and the Farm Boy]]'',<ref name="Amazon">{{Amazon|url=Star-Wars-Hope-Illustrated-Novel/dp/1484709128|text=''A New Hope Illustrated Novel''}}</ref> ''[[The Empire Strikes Back: So You Want to Be a Jedi?]]'', ''[[Return of the Jedi: Beware the Power of the Dark Side!]]'' and the [[Star Wars: Galaxy's Edge (comic series)|''Star Wars: Galaxy's Edge'' comic series]].<ref name="SW-Marvel Journeys to Batuu in New Star Wars: Galaxy's Edge Comic - Exclusive">{{SW|url=news/marvel-star-wars-galaxys-edge-comic-exclusive|text=Marvel Journeys to Batuu in New ''Star Wars: Galaxy's Edge'' Comic - Exclusive}}</ref>

McCaig planned to complete a comic titled "[[In a Future, Far, Far Away...]]" for the [[2005]] graphic novel anthology ''[[Star Wars: Visionaries]]'', which would have followed [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] and [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] thousands of years after the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], but was unable to complete it due to his obligations on ''Revenge of the Sith''.<ref name="JCF">{{JCFCite|url=posts/56657555|board=Literature|thread=Lostworlds & Lost Words: Cancelled Media|user=ColeFardreamer|date=2020-05-18|archiveurl=https://archive.md/s36cX}}</ref>

Iain McCaig was brought in to sketch characters for the ''[[Star Wars: The High Republic]]'' publishing campaign, a series released in [[2021]].<ref name="High Republic">{{SWYouTube|xCat5fXRyyU|Star Wars: The High Republic &#124; Announcement Trailer|sw_url=video/announce-trailer-star-wars-the-high-republic}}</ref>

